- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category, as the paper discusses the behaviour of lambda-terms and PCF programs, which are programming languages. 
- cs.TCS (Theoretical Computer Science) is a broad category that encompasses many topics related to the theoretical foundations of computer science, including game semantics and concurrency theory, which are relevant to this paper. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper deals with the definition of innocence in the context of games, which can be seen as a type of algorithmic problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely, but still possible, as the paper deals with the behaviour of agents (i.e., strategies) in interactive settings, which is a topic relevant to AI.
